com.tempodb

Class Rollup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tempodb.Rollup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Rollup
extends Object
implements Serializable
    The representation of a rollup of a single Series. A Rollup allows you to specify a time period and folding function for a DataPoint query. A Rollup represents a reduction in the amount of data returned to you. For instance, if you want to know the hourly average of a range of data, the Rollup is specified as: 

      import org.joda.time.Period;

  Rollup rollup = new Rollup(Period.hours(1), Fold.SUM);
    Since:
    1.0.0
